data.title: Quite a Let Down!
data.text:
In June, had a pleasant meal here. Tonight, no. Felt the need to balance comments of earlier impression. Hope that this was just an "off" dining experience and isolated scenario. 

My order of steak fajitas was rubbery and inedible! Imagine filling a tortilla with steak, peppers, onions, and toppings, then trying to take a bite but it's impossible because the meat stretches but doesn't break. Yuck!

Not sure what might cause this. Whatever the reason, need to caution diners on ordering steak fajiitas based on my experience.

So disappointing!

Plusses:
Friendly waitress and quick service

Ambience:
Background music blaring while the television WITH SOUND is tuned in to a mixed martial arts show!

data.title: Authentic Delicious Dinner
data.text:
+ Generous portions
+ Self-serve salsa/condiment bar (especially enjoyed the mild avocado sauce)
+ Attentive service
+ Quick delivery of food the evening we were there

Had the carne asada which I'd order again. 

It's a homey compact restaurant. ☺

A bit hard to find because restaurant is not visible from Pacific Highway, and it's tucked among some Asian businesses in a strip mall. See photos for the sign that marks where restaurant is.

data.title: Good Mexican food
data.text: Was looking for a good Mexican restaurant around our area. Family run establishment and food was good. Not the best but good and portion size was big. Good home cooking.

data.title: excelentes tacos
data.text: Un lugar pequeño,pero acogedor, con buena atención, limpio y sencillo, pero vale la pena comer, si le hace honor a su nombre, estos tacos son una tentacion.
